  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I remove the montage sound from video?",
  "response": "Removing sound from a video, such as a montage or background music, can be accomplished using various video editing software tools. Here are some methods you can try:\n\n### Using Video Editing Software\n\n1. **Adobe Premiere Pro**:\n   - Import your video into Premiere Pro.\n   - Drag the video onto the timeline.\n   - Right-click on the audio track and select **Unlink** to separate the audio from the video.\n   - Select the audio track and press **Delete** to remove it.\n   - Export your video without sound.\n\n2. **Final Cut Pro**:\n   - Import your video and add it to the timeline.\n   - Right-click on the audio component and choose **Detach Audio**.\n   - Delete the audio track and export your video.\n\n3. **iMovie (Mac)**:\n   - Import your video and add it to the timeline.\n   - Select the video clip, then go to the audio options in the inspector.\n   - Adjust the volume slider to zero, or right-click the clip and choose **Detach Audio** and then delete it.\n   - Export your video.\n\n4. **Windows Movie Maker**:\n   - Import your video into Movie Maker.\n   - Right-click on the video in the timeline and select **Audio** > **Mute**.\n   - Save or export your video.\n\n### Using Online Tools\n\n1. **Kapwing**:\n   - Go to the Kapwing website and upload your video.\n   - Use the editing tools to mute or remove the audio.\n   - Export the edited video.\n\n2. **Clideo**:\n   - Go to Clideo's website and upload your video.\n   - Use the \u201cMute Video\u201d tool to remove the sound.\n   - Download the final video without sound.\n\n3. **VEED.IO**:\n   - Upload your video on VEED.IO.\n   - You can find an option to mute or delete the audio.\n   - Export the video without the sound.\n\n### Using VLC Media Player\n\nIf you only want to export a video without sound but don't need to edit it:\n1. Open the video in VLC.\n2. Go to **Media** > **Convert/Save**.\n3. Add your video file and click **Convert/Save**.\n4. In the Profile section, select a video format.\n5. Click on the wrench icon (Edit selected profile).\n6. Go to the **Audio codec** tab and uncheck the **Audio** checkbox.\n7. Save your settings and proceed with the conversion.\n\nBy following these steps using any of the outlined methods, you should be able to effectively remove the sound from your video.",
